    "# Neural Network"

   ],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd #for manipulating the data set\n",
    "import tensorflow\n",
    "from tensorflow import keras #first had to install the keras package used for image neural network processing on anaconda\n",
    "from keras.models import Model, Sequential\n",
    "from keras.layers import Dense, Activation\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split #for splitting the data into train and test\n",
    "import keras.backend as K\n",
    "K.clear_session()\n",
    "from keras import optimizers\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler #for zero-mean and unit variance\n",
    "sc = StandardScaler()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next we import the data from http://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/Forest+type+mapping and note that it was already separated into training and testing in .csv format. \n",
    "\n",
    "The data info: \"This data set contains training and testing data from a remote sensing study which mapped different forest types based on their spectral characteristics at visible-to-near infrared wavelengths, using ASTER satellite imagery. The output (forest type map) can be used to identify and/or quantify the ecosystem services (e.g. carbon storage, erosion protection) provided by the forest.\"\n",
    "\n",
    "The classes are: \"'s' ('Sugi' forest), 'h' ('Hinoki' forest), 'd' ('Mixed deciduous' forest), 'o' ('Other' non-forest land)\"\n",
    "\n",
    "The features represent spectral data consisting of 9 spectral bands and 18 \"similarity measures calculated from the IDW interpolated values\".\n",
    "\n",
    "The paper http://www.cr.chiba-u.jp/~tateishi-lab/pdf/2011/Using%20geographically%202011.pdf utilized an SVM algorithm and we hope to improve on its accuracy by using a simple neural network below.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(198, 28)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#the data as provided by the UCI database already split\n",
    "df_train = pd.read_csv('training.csv',delim_whitespace=False)\n",
    "df_test = pd.read_csv('testing.csv',delim_whitespace=False)\n",
    "df_test.shape #325 examples of 27 features each\n",
    "df_train.shape #198 examples of 27 features each - 62:38 ratio of test v. train"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class_mapping={label:idx for idx,label in enumerate(np.unique(df_train['class']))} # change the class names which are strings to integers\n",
    "df_train['class']=df_train['class'].map(class_mapping)\n",
    "class_mapping={label:idx for idx,label in enumerate(np.unique(df_test['class']))}\n",
    "df_test['class']=df_test['class'].map(class_mapping)\n",
    "X_train, y_train = df_train.iloc[:, 1:].values, df_train.iloc[:, 0].values # the first column is class header\n",
    "X_test, y_test = df_test.iloc[:, 1:].values, df_test.iloc[:, 0].values # the first column is class header\n",
    "X_train = sc.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test = sc.fit_transform(X_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we create a very simple network.  The features are:\n",
    "*  We have one hidden layer with `nh=100` units.  \n",
    "*  One output layer with `nout=4` units, one for each of the 4 possible classes\n",
    "*  The output activation is `softmax`, which is used for multi-class targets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "WARNING:tensorflow:From C:\\Users\\munib\\Anaconda3\\lib\\site-packages\\tensorflow\\python\\framework\\op_def_library.py:263: colocate_with (from tensorflow.python.framework.ops) is deprecated and will be removed in a future version.\n",
      "Instructions for updating:\n",
      "Colocations handled automatically by placer.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nin = X_train.shape[1]  # dimension of input data\n",
    "nh = 100     # number of hidden units\n",
    "nout = 4   # number of outputs = 4 since there are 4 classes\n",
    "model = Sequential()\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nh, input_shape=(nin,), activation='sigmoid', name='hidden')) # we keep the activation function as a sigmoid\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nout, activation='softmax', name='output'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",

      "=================================================================\n",
      "hidden (Dense)               (None, 100)               2800      \n",
      "_________________________________________________________________\n",
      "output (Dense)               (None, 4)                 404       \n",
      "=================================================================\n",
      "Total params: 3,204\n",
      "Trainable params: 3,204\n",
      "Non-trainable params: 0\n",
      "_________________________________________________________________\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "model.summary() #we will be training all of the parameters in the neural network"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model.compile(optimizer=tensorflow.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(0.001), # doing gradient descent to update te parameters with learning rate of 0.001\n",
    "             loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', #loss function instead of squared difference sparse categorical crossentropy due to multi-class system\n",
    "             metrics=['accuracy'])"
   ]

    "from keras.layers import LeakyReLU # perhaps neurons are dying and not being updated due to negative values making gradient 0 so try LEaky-relu\n",
    "\n",
    "# instead of model.add(Activation('relu'))\n",
    "# use\n",
    "K.clear_session()\n",
    "model = Sequential()\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nout, activation='softmax', name='output'))\n",
    "model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer=tensorflow.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(0.001),\n",
    "             loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",

    "#the data as manually concatenated in excel of training and test as provided by the database\n",
    "df= pd.read_csv('data.csv',delim_whitespace=False)\n",
    "class_mapping={label:idx for idx,label in enumerate(np.unique(df['class']))}\n",
    "df['class']=df['class'].map(class_mapping)\n",
    "X, y = df.iloc[:, 1:].values, df.iloc[:, 0].values # the first column is class header\n",
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.3) # we will be using 70:30 for train vs. test as we want to maximize the training data size and the ratio has also shown better performance in nerual algorithm processing\n",
    "X_train = sc.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test = sc.fit_transform(X_test)"

    "# SIGMOID GRADIENT DESCENT\n",
    "K.clear_session()\n",
    "nin = X_train.shape[1]  # dimension of input data\n",
    "nh = 100     # number of hidden units\n",
    "nout = 4   # number of outputs = 4 since there are 4 classes\n",
    "model = Sequential()\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nh, input_shape=(nin,), activation='sigmoid', name='hidden')) # we keep the activation function as a sigmoid\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nout, activation='softmax', name='output'))\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer=tensorflow.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(0.001), # doing gradient descent to update te parameters with learning rate of 0.001\n",
    "             loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy', #loss function instead of squared difference sparse categorical crossentropy due to multi-class system\n",
    "             metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
    "model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=2000, batch_size=32, validation_data=(X_test,y_test))"
   ]

    "# LEAKY RELU GRADIENT DESCENT\n",
    "from keras.layers import LeakyReLU # perhaps neuros are dying and not being updated due to negative values making gradient 0 so try LEaky-relu\n",
    "\n",
    "# instead of model.add(Activation('relu'))\n",
    "# use\n",
    "K.clear_session()\n",
    "model = Sequential()\n",
    "model.add(Dense(nout, activation='softmax', name='output'))\n",
    "model.add(LeakyReLU(alpha=0.1))\n",
    "model.compile(optimizer=tensorflow.train.GradientDescentOptimizer(0.001),\n",
    "             loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',\n",
    "             metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
    "model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=2000, batch_size=32, validation_data=(X_test,y_test))"
